  "tldr": [
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/ai",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "The Control Plane Was the Point: Revisiting autofz in the LLM Era",
      "url": "https://yfu.tw/blog/en/autofz-revisited/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/gwxqmh",
      "score": 1,
      "comments": 0,
      "author": "yufu",
      "published": "2026-07-02T05:19:10Z",
      "bullets": [
        "LLMs can modernize autofz by acting as intelligent control planes, dynamically coordinating diverse fuzzing engines like AFL and LibFuzzer.",
        "Generative AI transforms cooperative fuzzing by automating seed generation and mutator selection, optimizing path coverage over traditional static heuristics.",
        "The architectural separation of control and execution in autofz serves as a blueprint for coordinating multi-agent LLM security testing systems."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "What are you doing this week?",
      "url": "https://lobste.rs/s/qzrdzu",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/qzrdzu",
      "score": 11,
      "comments": 9,
      "author": "caius",
      "published": "2026-06-29T07:55:57Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Developers share weekly progress on system tools, compiler design, and self-hosted deployments using modern stacks like Rust, Go, and SQLite.",
        "The community emphasizes balancing active feature shipping with intentional downtime to prevent developer burnout and technical debt.",
        "Engineers exchange feedback on niche libraries, database schema migrations, and optimizing CI/CD pipelines for personal hobby projects."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "Unprivileged root via an out-of-bounds write in the FUSE readdir cache (CVE-2026-31694)",
      "url": "https://cyberstan.co.uk/fuse-readdir-oob/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/0kc445",
      "score": 7,
      "comments": 2,
      "author": "fro",
      "published": "2026-07-02T00:36:55Z",
      "bullets": [
        "CVE-2026-31694 exposes Linux kernels to local privilege escalation via an out-of-bounds write in FUSE memory management.",
        "Unprivileged local attackers can exploit the readdir cache flaw to corrupt kernel memory and execute arbitrary code as root.",
        "Administrators should immediately patch affected Linux kernels, focusing on multi-tenant environments and container hosts using user-space filesystems."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/devops",
      "category": "devops",
      "title": "OpenFeature - Standardizing Feature Flagging for Everyone",
      "url": "https://openfeature.dev/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/4ttyrk",
      "score": 3,
      "comments": 0,
      "author": "datboi",
      "published": "2026-07-02T02:31:35Z",
      "bullets": [
        "OpenFeature is a CNCF incubating project establishing a vendor-agnostic standard and unified API specification for cloud-native feature flagging.",
        "It prevents vendor lock-in, enabling seamless migration between backends like LaunchDarkly, Unleash, Flagsmith, or custom in-house tooling without code rewrites.",
        "The ecosystem supports major languages including Go, Java, and Python, offering native Kubernetes integration for GitOps-friendly feature management."
      ]
    },
